Aim

The aim of this report is to reproduce the hypothesis-generating data analyses in the original research article by Ma, Karthik, LÃ¶vrot, et al.1

Background

To be added.

Breast cancer stem-like cells (BSC).

Data aquisition

To further explore ERÎ² function in BSCs, we performed whole-transcriptome analysis of mammospheres (MCF7S) incubated with vehicle control, or 10nM DPN.

All the procedures and Affymetrix CEL files are available through the Gene Expression Omnibus (GEO) Database under accession number GSE56139.

Data munging

Microarray data preprocessing

Affymetrix microarray CEL files for GSE56139 was retrieved using the GEOquery package2. Probe intensities were extracted from CEL files and background corrected, normalized and summarized to probeset expression using the rma function from the oligo package3 with the default settings. Probesets were mapped to Entrez Gene IDs using the hta20transcriptcluster.db package.

Initial data explorations

Since expression values are log2 transformed intensity values, a difference in expression by one unit corresponds to a two-fold mean change in probe intensities.

Differential expression analysis

Expression data was collapsed to gene level using a non-specific filter keeping only the probesets with highest interquartile range in the case of multiple mappings to the same Entrez Gene ID.

eset <- genefilter::featureFilter(erbeta)

DPN induced changes in gene expression were assessed with moderated t-tests using the limma package4. Multiple testing was controlled by calculating the expected false discovery rate (FDR) according to Benjamini & Hochberg.

eset <- eset[, eset$cellcd == "MCF7S" & eset$armcd %in% c("C", "D")]
eset$armcd <- eset$armcd[drop = TRUE]

design <- model.matrix(~ armcd, data = pData(eset))
fit <- lmFit(eset, design)
fit <- contrasts.fit(fit, coefficients = "armcdD")
fit <- eBayes(fit)
tab <- topTable(fit, number = nrow(eset), adjust.method = "BH")

Transcriptome changes after DPN treatment in MCF7S revealed a distinct gene expression pattern: 75 transcripts were differentially regulated upon DPN treatment compared to the control group (moderated t-tests, nominal P < 0.0005, FDR â 0.15).

Gene set enrichment analysis

To assess the biological relevance of the distinct gene expression pattern, we performed gene set enrichment analyses (GSEA) of the canonical pathways gene-set collection in the Molecular Signatures Database (Broad Institute). Seven gene sets were significantly enriched in DPN-treated mammospheres as compared to control (FDR < 0.10, Supplementary Table 3) with the majority related to glycolytic metabolism and with REACTOME_GLYCOLYSIS as top pathway (FDR < 0.001, Figure 4A).

Enrichment analyses of canonical pathways gene-set collections in the Molecular Signatures Database (Broad Institute) were performed using the GSEA Software (Broad Institute)5 with genes pre-ranked according to the moderated t-test statistics.

The original analysis was performed using R version 3.2.3, in particular the hta20sttranscriptcluster.db annotation package (version 8.3.1) was used. Here, weâve instead used the hta20transcriptcluster.db annotation package â no âstâ in the package name â as of R version 3.3 and higher, see https://support.bioconductor.org/p/91448/.
